ault.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_kinard_ver01/data/sn95047246/00529042115/1945092701/0568.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95047246/1945-09-27/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_kinard_ver01/data/sn95047246/00529042115/1945092701/0568.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95047246/1945-09-27/ed-1/?sp=4"], "batch": ["fu_kinard_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/florida/", "2/united states/florida/hernando/", "3/united states/florida/hernando/brooksville/"], "contributor": ["university of florida"], "date": "1945-09-27", "dates": ["1945-09-27"], "description": ["PAGE FOUR Dept Commerce To Be Expanded Washington Sept 20 Secre tary of Commerce Wallace today announced a departmental reor ganization plan calling for vigor ous expansion of facilities to pro mote foreign trade and aid busi nessespecially small business He told a press conference that during reconversion and postwar adjustment the commerce depart ment must be prepared to pull its weight in the program of the ad ministration to assure full profit able production and full gainful employment He said he would seek three new assistant secretaries to be respons ible for international trade indus trial economy and small business The department now has one as sistant secretary for air commerce and related technical services Proposals have been submitted to congress for additional legisla tion and funds needed to put the program into operation although the department already is in a po sition to carry out a substantial part of it he said United the suggested program the department would provide 1 A revitalized foreign trade service to cooperate with the state department in formulating com mercial policy and promoting vig orously a high level 